{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"958e4f86-86df-4521-bf84-1abecfc9fd62","content":"On macOS, when a NativeAOT app crashes, look in these locations:\n\n1. **Apple Crash Reports** — macOS automatically generates `.ips` (or `.crash`) files:\n   ```\n   ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n   /Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n   ```\n\n2. **Core dumps** — if enabled:\n   ```bash\n   ulimit -c unlimited   # enable before running your app\n   ```\n   Cores are written to `/cores/core.<pid>`.\n\n3. **Console.app** — open it and check under **Crash Reports** for your process name.\n\nThe `.ips` crash report includes the faulting thread, stack trace, and register state — often enough to diagnose the issue without a full core dump.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"85c945dd-31dd-4895-b4e7-b242c03442ca","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT .NET app on macOS, without `createdump`. This is a general knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":246,"requestId":"D822:1E62:297566F:2DCAE1C:69FBEFE2"},"id":"116dd7ae-6e8e-427d-8fda-b222344e7f8c","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:50:33.930Z","parentId":"9b04bccc-11f0-45fd-99e4-b3c987fe366a"}
